1 Dataset Preparation

1.1 Importing Dataset

#import data
data_camera_bdm <- read.csv('Camera_BDM.csv')

#removing unnecessary variables*
data_camera_bdm <- data_camera_bdm[-c(1,2,3,4,5,9,12,13)]
#*they are not my variables of interest

#renaming a typo in the data set
data_camera_bdm <- rename(data_camera_bdm, Camera_utilitarian=Camera_utilitiarian)

#add a variable: frequency in using camera per week, combination of taking pictures and taking videos in a week
data_camera_bdm$Camera_freq_week <-
  data_camera_bdm$Pictures_week +
  data_camera_bdm$Videos_week
  
#add a variable: total number of services used, combination of all services used in the past 12 months
data_camera_bdm$No_Services <-
  data_camera_bdm$Services_Facebook +
  data_camera_bdm$Services_Instagram +
  data_camera_bdm$Services_Snapchat +
  data_camera_bdm$Services_Twitter +
  data_camera_bdm$Services_LinkedIn +
  data_camera_bdm$Services_WhatsApp

#convert into factors
data_camera_bdm$Services_Facebook <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_Facebook)
data_camera_bdm$Services_Instagram <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_Instagram)
data_camera_bdm$Services_Snapchat <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_Snapchat)
data_camera_bdm$Services_Twitter <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_Twitter)
data_camera_bdm$Services_LinkedIn <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_LinkedIn)
data_camera_bdm$Services_WhatsApp <- as.factor(data_camera_bdm$Services_WhatsApp)

1.5.2 Boxcox Transformation

train_data$BDM_main_boxcox <- (train_data$BDM_main^-0.05-1)/-0.05
train_data$BDM_front_boxcox <- ((train_data$BDM_front+1)^-0.05-1)/-0.05
train_data$BDM_both_boxcox <- (train_data$BDM_both^-0.05-1)/-0.05
train_data$Camera_freq_week_boxcox <- ((train_data$Camera_freq_week+1)^-0.05-1)/-0.05

2 Analysis

2.1 Exploratory Data Analysis

2.1.1 Paired Sample T-Test BDM_Main-BDM_Front

d1 <- with(train_data, BDM_main_boxcox - BDM_front_boxcox)
shapiro.test(d1)
## 
##  Shapiro-Wilk normality test
## 
## data:  d1
## W = 0.90256, p-value = 2.84e-09
#the difference (d) between each pair of value is not normal, therefore Wilcoxon signed rank test is used
wilcox.test(train_data$BDM_main_boxcox, train_data$BDM_front_boxcox, paired = TRUE, alternative = "two.sided")
## 
##  Wilcoxon signed rank test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  train_data$BDM_main_boxcox and train_data$BDM_front_boxcox
## V = 9936, p-value = 0.0002588
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0

2.2.14 Repeated Cross Validation

Whole Data Boxcox Transformation

data_camera_bdm$BDM_main_boxcox <- (data_camera_bdm$BDM_main^-0.05-1)/-0.05
data_camera_bdm$BDM_front_boxcox <- ((data_camera_bdm$BDM_front+1)^-0.05-1)/-0.05
data_camera_bdm$BDM_both_boxcox <- (data_camera_bdm$BDM_both^-0.05-1)/-0.05
data_camera_bdm$Camera_freq_week_boxcox <- ((data_camera_bdm$Camera_freq_week+1)^-0.05-1)/-0.05

Model Validation

set.seed(12345)
trmse1 <- c()
vrmse1 <- c()
for (i in 1:173) {
  training_index1 <- sample(nrow(data_camera_bdm),173)
  training_data1 <- data_camera_bdm[training_index1,]
  validation_data1 <- data_camera_bdm[-training_index1,]
  model1 <- lm(formula_main,training_data1)
  predictions1 <- predict(model1,validation_data1)
  trmse1 <- c(trmse1,sqrt(mean(model1$residuals**2)))
  vrmse1 <- c(vrmse1,sqrt(mean((predictions1-validation_data1$BDM_main_boxcox)**2)))
  }

boxplot(trmse1,vrmse1,names=c("training","validation"))

set.seed(12345)

vrmse2 <- c()

  training_index2 <- sample(nrow(data_camera_bdm),173)
  training_data2 <- data_camera_bdm[training_index2,]
  validation_data2 <- data_camera_bdm[-training_index2,]
  model2 <- lm(formula_front,training_data2)
  predictions2 <- predict(model2,validation_data2)
  trmse2 <- c(trmse2,sqrt(mean(model2$residuals**2)))
  vrmse2 <- c(vrmse2,sqrt(mean((predictions2-validation_data2$BDM_front_boxcox)**2)))
  }

boxplot(trmse2,vrmse2,names=c("training","validation"))
